HEADWORD: Radiotelegraphy
<hw>Ra`di*o*te*leg"ra*phy</hw>
<pr>(r⟦amac⟧`d⟦icr⟧*⟦ocr⟧*t⟦ecr⟧*l⟦ecr⟧g"r⟦adot⟧*f⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Radio-</ets> + <ets>telegraphy</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Telegraphy using the radiant energy of radio waves; wireless
telegraphy; -- the term adopted for use by the Radiotelegraphic
Convention of 1912.</def>⟦br⟧
